From mcmt84@yahoo.com  Fri Feb 28 20:03:35 2003
From: mcmt84@yahoo.com (Tom Smith)
Date: Fri, 28 Feb 2003 12:03:35 -0800 (PST)
Subject: [R-gui] Texmacs as an R gui
Message-ID: <20030228200335.86916.qmail@web41202.mail.yahoo.com>

On thing to keep an eye on as an R gui is Texmacs
(www.texmacs.org). It is a very good typesetting
program, but it is designed to have connections to
math programs like maxima or octave and now R. 

Right now, they mainly work in a terminal mode. The
advantage is that you can display graph results in
line with the output. See the following link for an
example:

http://mail.gnu.org/archive/html/texmacs-dev/2002-11/ps00000.ps

Which was buried in this email:

http://mail.gnu.org/archive/html/texmacs-dev/2002-11/msg00262.html

Eventually, they plan to also have workbook and
spreadsheet type interfaces. See:

http://mail.gnu.org/archive/html/texmacs-dev/2002-11/msg00256.html

Mike


